Work in Progress

Tracking Unemployment in Idaho

By Chris Amico, Danny DeBelius,
Jessica Pupovac and Matt Stiles

The jobless rate in Idaho is declining, but thousands in the Gem State remain unemployed following the 2008 financial crisis. Use this tool to track unemployment by county over time, read personal accounts of Idahoans still seeking work, and please tell us your story. About this data.

EDITOR'S NOTE: The Idaho Department of Labor won't update monthly unemployment data until March 23. In January and February the department is focused on “annual benchmarking,” a process of re-estimating and smoothing the data for accuracy and consistency. The release of unemployment data will resume its normal schedule by April.

    Share your story

    We want to know about your place in Idaho’s employment landscape. Tell us your story of losing a job, finding a job, or coping in between via email (unemployment@stateimpact.org) or voicemail (208-278-6154).

    Our goal is to share your stories to inspire and inform our audience. Please provide your name, plus an email address or phone number so we can contact you. We won’t publish your information without your consent.

    These Idaho residents already shared their stories. We'd love to hear yours!
